# Runtime theme state generated by theme-engine/theme-set.sh
current/

# DMS auto-generates these into ~/.config/niri/dms/ at runtime (each one is
# stamped "DO NOT EDIT - AUTO-GENERATED BY DMS") - some are machine-specific
# (outputs.kdl has hardcoded resolution/output names), so don't track them.
# dms/binds.kdl is the one exception: it's DMS/user-editable, not purely
# auto-generated, and we ship a starter set - so it stays tracked.
config/niri/dms/colors.kdl
config/niri/dms/layout.kdl
config/niri/dms/alttab.kdl
config/niri/dms/outputs.kdl
config/niri/dms/cursor.kdl
config/niri/dms/windowrules.kdl
config/niri/dms/wpblur.kdl

# DMS's own per-app "matugen" theme integration writes these directly into
# app config dirs we track - separate files, doesn't touch the configs we
# actually manage (alacritty.toml, settings.ini, config.kdl), but it's noise
# we don't want tracked. Same for niri's own defensive backups of config.kdl.
config/alacritty/dank-theme.toml
config/gtk-3.0/dank-colors.css
config/gtk-4.0/dank-colors.css
config/niri/config.kdl.backup*
config/niri/config.kdl.dmsbackup*

# Dynamic output from cachy-default-editor, not a source-controlled config -
# regenerates itself whenever you change the default editor via cachy-menu.
config/environment.d/editor.conf
